# WHAT IT IS
#   KumoMTA is a high-volume Mail Transfer Agent designed for
#   sending bulk mail (think email service providers, newsletter
#   senders, transactional ESPs).  Built from the ground up in
#   Rust to outscale every previous MTA on the same hardware,
#   with a Lua-based policy DSL (via mlua) for routing,
#   throttling, bounce classification, DKIM signing, SPF/DMARC
#   validation, and TLS handling.  The configurable
#   `kumo.on('main')` event-handler pattern lets operators
#   express arbitrary mail-pipeline policy entirely in Lua.
#
#   Kafka integration is plumbed through the workspace's
#   `mod-kafka` crate (which direct-depends on
#   `rdkafka = "0.38"`) — kumod's `lua_deliver.rs` can produce
#   messages to Kafka topics for downstream analytics /
#   warehouse pipelines, while the same `mod-kafka` consumer
#   side lets kumod-fronted webhook receivers backpressure
#   against a Kafka queue.
#
#   The companion CLI `kcli` (also part of the same workspace
#   under ./crates/kcli/) talks to a running kumod via the
#   kumo-api-client and exposes the operator surface (queue
#   inspection, bounce-table edits, in-flight message admin,
#   etc.).  This completion file covers only the `kumod`
#   daemon binary.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from crates/kumod/src/main.rs
#                       clap-derive `Opt` struct; extracted
#                       via `gh api repos/KumoCorp/kumomta/
#                       contents/crates/kumod/src/main.rs`)
#
#   kumod [OPTIONS] [-- <SCRIPT-ARGS>...]
#
#   Options:
#     --policy <PATH>                Lua policy file to load
#                                    [default: /opt/kumomta/
#                                    etc/policy/init.lua]
#     --validate                     Run the policy init
#                                    function in validation
#                                    mode, then stop.  In
#                                    validation mode,
#                                    listeners are NOT started
#                                    and the spool is NOT
#                                    acquired.
#     --script                       Rather than spawning
#                                    kumod in service mode,
#                                    execute the policy script
#                                    as a standalone script
#                                    and then exit.  Use
#                                    `kumo.on('main')` to
#                                    define the entry point;
#                                    pass arguments via
#                                    --script-args or the
#                                    trailing `-- ARGS...`
#                                    positional list.
#     --diag-log-dir <DIR>           Directory where diagnostic
#                                    log files will be placed.
#                                    If omitted, diagnostics
#                                    are printed to stderr.
#     --diag-format <FORMAT>         How diagnostic logs render
#                                    [default: full]
#                                    (full | compact | pretty
#                                    | json) — full / compact
#                                    / pretty are for human
#                                    consumption; json outputs
#                                    machine-readable records.
#     --dump-openapi-spec            Output the OpenAPI spec
#                                    JSON to stdout instead of
#                                    running the daemon.
#     --dump-lruttl-caches           Output the list of LruTtl
#                                    caches to stdout instead
#                                    of running the daemon.
#     --dump-metric-metadata         Output the list of metric
#                                    metadata to stdout instead
#                                    of running the daemon.
#     --user <USER>                  Required if started as
#                                    root.  Specifies which
#                                    user to run as once
#                                    privileges have been
#                                    dropped.  Set --user root
#                                    explicitly if you truly
#                                    wish to run as root.
#     --script-args <ARG>            (Deprecated) List of
#                                    arguments to pass to
#                                    `main` event when running
#                                    in --script mode.  Use
#                                    the trailing `-- ARGS...`
#                                    positional list instead.
#                                    Requires --script.
#
#   Trailing positional  (when --script is used):
#     -- <ARG>...                    Arguments forwarded to the
#                                    Lua `main` event.
#                                    Requires --script.
#
#   Standard clap auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `rdkafka = "0.38"` declared in
#   workspace Cargo.toml + workspace member `mod-kafka` which
#   uses `rdkafka.workspace=true` — `rdkafka` is THE canonical
#   Rust Apache Kafka client, maintained by Federico Giraud
#   (fede1024) and the rust-rdkafka contributors at the
#   fede1024/rust-rdkafka repository (1,800+ stars; a typed
#   safe Rust wrapper around Confluent's official C library
#   `librdkafka` — the same `librdkafka` that powers
#   confluent-kafka-go (Go), confluent-kafka-python (Python),
#   confluent-kafka-dotnet (C#), and node-rdkafka (Node.js),
#   making it the de-facto standard Kafka client for any
#   language with a C FFI; used by KumoCorp/kumomta,
#   delta-io/kafka-delta-ingest, fede1024/kafka-view,
#   chirpstack/chirpstack, MaterializeInc/materialize,
#   getsentry/relay, juspay/hyperswitch, PostHog/posthog,
#   feldera/feldera, estuary/flow, postmates/cernan,
#   cloudevents/sdk-rust, AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenCue,
#   memgraph/example-streaming-app, and dozens of other
#   production Rust applications that produce / consume Kafka
#   messages).
#   `rdkafka` exposes the typed `ClientConfig::new()
#   .set("bootstrap.servers", "kafka:9092")
#   .set("group.id", "consumer-group")
#   .set("enable.auto.commit", "false")
#   .set("auto.offset.reset", "earliest")
#   .set("compression.type", "lz4")
#   .set("session.timeout.ms", "6000")
#   .set("statistics.interval.ms", "500")
#   .create::<StreamConsumer>()?` builder pattern, the typed
#   `StreamConsumer` / `BaseConsumer` consumer variants with
#   `consumer.subscribe(&["topic"])` /
#   `consumer.recv().await? -> BorrowedMessage` /
#   `consumer.commit_message(&message, CommitMode::Async)` /
#   `consumer.store_offset_from_message(&message)` /
#   `consumer.seek(topic, partition, offset, timeout)` /
#   `consumer.assignment()` / `consumer.subscription()`, the
#   typed `FutureProducer` / `BaseProducer` /
#   `ThreadedProducer` producer variants with
#   `producer.send(FutureRecord::to("topic")
#   .key("key").payload("payload"), timeout).await? ->
#   (partition, offset)`, the typed `Message<'_>` trait with
#   `msg.topic()` / `msg.partition()` / `msg.offset()` /
#   `msg.key()` / `msg.payload()` / `msg.headers()` /
#   `msg.timestamp()` accessors, the typed `OwnedHeaders` /
#   `BorrowedHeaders` / `HeaderRef` API for record metadata,
#   the typed `Timeout::After(duration)` /
#   `Timeout::Never` polling timeout primitive, every typed
#   `KafkaError` variant (`BrokerNotAvailable`,
#   `MessageTimedOut`, `OffsetOutOfRange`, `PartitionEOF`,
#   `MessageTooLarge`, `UnknownTopicOrPartition`,
#   `OffsetMetadataTooLarge`, `NetworkException`,
#   `GroupAuthorizationFailed`, etc.),
#   the `AdminClient::create_topics(topics, opts).await?` /
#   `delete_topics(names, opts)` / `describe_configs(...)` /
#   `alter_configs(...)` administration interface, the
#   typed `StatisticsContext` /  `ConsumerContext` /
#   `ProducerContext` context-trait hooks for emitting
#   `client.statistics()` JSON snapshots, observing
#   `assignment_lost` / `pre_rebalance` / `post_rebalance`
#   consumer-group rebalances, and intercepting
#   `delivery(...)` producer acknowledgements.
#   kumomta's `crates/mod-kafka/src/lib.rs` exposes
#   `kumo.kafka.{producer,consumer}.new(...)` Lua bindings
#   wrapping a typed `FutureProducer` / `StreamConsumer`
#   constructed from the user-policy `kumo.on(...)` callbacks.
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/KumoCorp/kumomta/contents/Cargo.toml
#       → workspace.dependencies: rdkafka = "0.38"
#       → [workspace] members include crates/kumod,
#                                      crates/mod-kafka,
#                                      crates/kcli, etc.
#     gh api repos/KumoCorp/kumomta/contents/crates/
#         mod-kafka/Cargo.toml
#       → rdkafka.workspace=true
#       → mlua = { workspace=true, features=["vendored",
#                                             "lua54",
#                                             "async",
#                                             "send",
#                                             "serialize"] }
#     gh api repos/KumoCorp/kumomta/contents/crates/kumod/
#         src/main.rs
#       → #[derive(Parser)] struct Opt { policy,
#                                          validate, script,
#                                          diag_log_dir,
#                                          diag_format,
#                                          dump_openapi_spec,
#                                          dump_lruttl_caches,
#                                          dump_metric_metadata,
#                                          user,
#                                          legacy_script_args,
#                                          script_args }
#       → /// KumoMTA Daemon.
#       → /// Full docs available at: <https://docs.kumomta.
#         com>
#   This entry is the Rust=162 leader bump that OPENS Axis 107
#   (Apache Kafka client via rdkafka) at 1/0/0.  Pairing Go
#   and TS-Node bumps will follow at R1016 and R1017 (Go=162
#   candidates IBM/sarama or confluent-kafka-go consumers;
#   TS-Node=162 candidates kafkajs / node-rdkafka /
#   @confluentinc/kafka-javascript users).
#
#   No completion for `kumod` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_kumod() {
    _arguments -s \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
        '--policy=[Lua policy file (default /opt/kumomta/etc/policy/init.lua)]:policy:_files -g "*.lua"' \
        '--validate[run policy init in validation mode then stop]' \
        '--script[execute the policy script as standalone then exit]' \
        '--diag-log-dir=[directory for diagnostic log files (default stderr)]:dir:_files -/' \
        '--diag-format=[diagnostic log format (default full)]:format:(full compact pretty json)' \
        '--dump-openapi-spec[output OpenAPI spec JSON to stdout]' \
        '--dump-lruttl-caches[output list of LruTtl caches to stdout]' \
        '--dump-metric-metadata[output list of metric metadata to stdout]' \
        '--user=[user to run as once privileges dropped (required if root)]:user:_users' \
        '*--script-args=[args to pass to main event (deprecated; requires --script)]:arg:' \
        '*::script args (after --, requires --script):'
}

_kumod "$@"
